    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-06T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/10–651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Deputy Representative on the North Atlantic
                        Council</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SCM1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spofford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d166fn1">Repeated to Paris for <persName corresp="#p_MDI1"
                            >MacArthur</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SMGCVR1"
                            >Schuyler</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-06T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 6, 1951—4 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Depto1">Depto</gloss> 427. 1. Ref <gloss target="#t_Todep1"
                        >Todep</gloss> 214.<note n="2" xml:id="d166fn2">Not printed, but see
                        footnote 3, <ref target="#pg_287">p. 287</ref>.</note> At 68th mtg <gloss
                        target="#t_CD1">CD</gloss> on Fr initiative directed <gloss target="#t_WG1"
                        >WG</gloss> to implement Ottawa infrastructure agrmt. Expect <gloss
                        target="#t_WG1">WG</gloss> meet Wednesday.</p>
                <pb facs="0335" n="297" xml:id="pg_297"/>
                <p>2. If US does not have position by Tuesday, real danger infrastructure negots may
                    be delayed once again as knowledge of US position wld appear indispensable to
                    any real progress in formulating arrangements for implementing Ottawa agrmt.
                    Delay for any reason wld, of course, prejudice <gloss target="#t_SHAPE1"
                        >SHAPE</gloss> mil position, which is primary concern, but delay for such a
                    reason wld also seriously undermine Eur confidence in <gloss target="#t_CD1"
                        >CD</gloss> as effective working agency in <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> setup. This consideration particularly valid in view of last
                    summer’s long delays and eleventh hour ministerial settlement Ottawa. Nor can
                    entirely discount possibility that Fr may act on <persName corresp="#p_MR2"
                        >Mayer</persName>’s repeated declarations at Ottawa that Fr wld not continue
                    unilaterally to advance funds for infrastructure after Oct 1. Such action
                    especially unfortunate if US alone of all member nations without instructions on
                    administrative details for implementing substance Ottawa settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SCM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spofford</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
